edge: In the movie 'Coolie No. 1', Varun Dhawan plays the dual role of Raju Coolie.
Varun Dhawan portrays Kunwar Raj Pratapsingh, another character in 'Coolie No. 1'.
Sara Ali Khan acts as Sarah Pratapsingh, also known as Sarah Rozario, in the film.
In 'Coolie No. 1', Paresh Rawal essays the character of Jeffrey Rozario, Sarah and Anju's father.
In 'Coolie No. 1', Jaaved Jaaferi plays the role of Pandit Jai Kishen or Secretary Jackson.
In the movie 'Coolie No. 1', Rajpal Yadav portrays Pinto Mama, Sarah and Anju's uncle and Jeffrey's brother-in-law.
In 'Coolie No. 1', Johnny Lever enacts the character of Inspector Jagjit Godbole.
In 'Coolie No. 1', Sahil Vaid plays the role of Deepak Mechanic, Anju's fiancé.
In 'Coolie No. 1', Shikha Talsania portrays Anjali 'Anju' Rozario, Jeffrey's daughter and Deepak's fiancé.
In 'Coolie No. 1', Vikas Verma enacts the character of Mahesh Pratapsingh, Mahendra's son.
In 'Coolie No. 1', Manoj Joshi essays the dual role of Driver as well as Shalini's father.
In 'Coolie No. 1', Shashi Kiran portrays Coolie Chacha, Raju's uncle.
In 'Coolie No. 1', Hemant Pandey plays Tambe, the owner of the South Indian Restaurant.
In 'Coolie No. 1', Farhad Samji enacts the role of Plumber at the Rozario Hotel.
In 'Coolie No. 1', Shibesh Debnath portrays Vishu Coolie, Raju's fellow porter.
In 'Coolie No. 1', Girdhar Swami plays the role of Casting director.
